pos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Philip de Kyme was born in 1124, in Lincolnshire, England, his father, Simon Fitzwilliam de Kyme, was 30 and his mother, Agnes Lindsey, was 31. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Hawise Kyme. He died on 28 November 1194, in Kyme, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1124–after 1189 bef 28 Nov 1194":"1124–28. november 1194","1124–1194":"1124–1194","1129–Female":"1129–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1143–1214":"1143–1214","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","1124–Female":"1124–Surnud","1154–1220":"1154–1220","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","–1258":"–1258","1094–1162":"1094–1162","1094–Female":"1094–Surnud","about 1162":"umbes 1162","after 1189 bef 28 Nov 1194":"28. november 1194","1220":"1220","1154":"1154","1143":"1143","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1194":"1194","1094":"1094","1160":"1160","1129":"1129","um 1160":"umbes 1160","1258":"1258","1214":"1214","1124":"1124","1145":"1145","Abt 1154":"umbes 1154","Sotby, Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England":"Sotby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hackthorn, Lincolnshire, England":"Hackthorn, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kyme, near Sleaford, Lincolnshire,England":"Kyme, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1124–after 1189 bef 28 Nov 1194":"1124–28. marraskuuta 1194","1124–1194":"1124–1194","1129–Female":"1129–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1143–1214":"1143–1214","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","1124–Female":"1124–Kuollut","1154–1220":"1154–1220","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","–1258":"–1258","1094–1162":"1094–1162","1094–Female":"1094–Kuollut","about 1162":"noin 1162","after 1189 bef 28 Nov 1